<BaseLayout title="KTEQ FAQ">
  <section>
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <h2>How can I listen to KTEQ?</h2>
    <p>You can tune in at 91.3 FM in the Rapid City area or stream online from our website. We’re currently working to improve our stream player for all browsers.</p>

    <h2>What kind of music does KTEQ play?</h2>
    <p>We air a diverse mix—rock, electronic, metal, indie, jazz, punk, experimental, classic country, and beyond—curated entirely by students and volunteers.</p>

    <h2>How can I become a DJ or volunteer?</h2>
    <p>Head over to our <a href="/get-involved">Get Involved</a> page to learn more about how to join KTEQ’s crew.</p>

    <h2>Can I submit music to be played?</h2>
    <p>Yes! We accept digital submissions via email. Physical media (vinyl, CDs, tapes) can be mailed to our campus address—just make sure it’s FCC clean.</p>

    <h2>Where can I find your public file?</h2>
    <p>Our FCC public inspection file is hosted online: <a href="https://publicfiles.fcc.gov/">publicfiles.fcc.gov</a>.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
